    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>Roger was having fun solving his problems until he found this one.As you know, an undirected connected graph with <b>N</b> nodes and <b>N-1</b> edges is called a tree.</p>\n<p>You are given an integer '<b>K</b>' and a tree consisting of '<b>N</b>' nodes. Each node '<b>i</b>' has a value <b>a(i)</b> associated with it.</p>\n<p>We call a path '<b>P</b>' of tree valid if following conditions are satisfied:</p>\n<p>\n<li> <b>P</b> has atleast 2 nodes associated with it.</li>\n</p><p>\n<li><b>Max a(u) - Min a(u) >= K</b> (<b>u</b> belongs to the nodes present in the chosen <b>P</b>).</li>\n</p>\n<p>Your task is to count the number of Valid Paths.</p>\n<p>\n<h3><b>Input</b></h3>\n</p>\n<p>The first line contains two space-separated integers <b>N</b> and <b>K</b>.</p>\n<p>The second line contains N space-separated positive integers <b>a(1),\u2009a(2),\u2009...,\u2009a(n)</b>.</p>\n<p>Then the next <b>n\u2009-\u20091</b> line each contain pair of integers <b>u</b> and <b>v</b> denoting that\n</p><p> there is an edge between <b>u</b> and <b>v</b>.</p>\n<p>\n<h3><b>Output</b></h3>\n</p>\n<p>Print the number of Valid Paths.</p>\n<p><b>Note:</b></p>\n<p>The nodes are numbered from <b>1</b> to <b>N</b>.</p>\n<p>\n<h3><b>Constraints</b></h3>\n</p>\n<p><b>1 \u2264 N \u2264 5000</b></p>\n<p><b>1 \u2264 u,v \u2264 N</b></p>\n<p><b>0 \u2264 K \u2264 10^9</b></p>\n<p><b>0 \u2264 ai\u2009\u2264 10^9</b></p>\n<p>\n<h3><b>Example</b></h3>\n</p>\n<p>\n<h3><b>Input:</b></h3>\n</p>\n<p>3 1</p>\n<p>1 2 3</p>\n<p>1 2</p>\n<p>2 3</p>\n<p>\n<h3><b>Output:</b></h3>\n</p>\n<p>3</p>\n",
